  <static seed="2311">
    <introduction><p>Simplify the expressions using the commutative, associative, and distributive properties.</p>
</introduction>
    <task>
      <statement><p><m>4-(3x-9)</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>13-3x</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>That first subtraction may be tricky. It may help to write that as addition of <m>-1</m> times the rest:</p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
4-(3x-9) \amp=4+(-1)(3x-9)\\
\amp=4+\Big(-1(3x)-(-1)(9)\Big)\\
\amp=4+(-3x+9)\\
\amp=4+(9-3x)\\
\amp=4+(9+(-3x))\\
\amp=(4+9)+(-3x)\\
\amp=13+(-3x)=13-3x
\end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement><p><m>9x+2(-2x+3)</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>5x+6</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>We start out with the distributive property and proceed from there:</p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
5x+9(-2x+3)\amp=5x+\Big(9(-2x)+9\cdot3\Big)\\
\amp=5x+(-18x+27)\\
\amp=(5x+(-18x))+27\\
\amp=-13x+27
\end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement><p><m>5(x-9)+4(x+4)</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0003"/></p>
</statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>9x-29</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
      <solution><p>We start out with the distributive property and proceed from there:</p>
<p><me>\begin{aligned}
\amp5(x-9)+4(x+4)\\
\amp=(5x-45)+(4x+16)\\
\amp=5x+(-45)+4x+16\amp\amp\text{skipping lots of formal algebra properties}\\
\amp=9x-29
\end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
    </task>
